'''{{nihongo|Oyabun|親分|}}''' is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] word meaning "father figure" or "boss".  It is traditionally used by  [[yakuza]] members to describe their boss or Godfather. ''Hachi'', the sidekick of ''Heiji'' in the story and TV series [[Zenigata Heiji]] refers to ''Heiji'' as oyabun.
 
